        "61043": {
          "vnum": 61043,
          "name": "Scribe`s Quarters",
          "description": "The Scribe's quarters are modest, a dusty square of stone filled by a small cot, an old ink-spotted wooden tabletop, and several rows of scroll-filled glass shelves. A copper pot of ink rests upon the table with a quill, along with a row of small candles, each having a distinct colour and mark. Behind the table sits a plain round stool.",
